# 🔧 System Calls Used

The project demonstrates practical use of:

- `open()`
- `read()`
- `write()`
- `close()`
- `creat()`
- `unlink()`
- `rename()`
- `stat()`
- `access()`
- `getcwd()`
- `chdir()`
- `opendir()`
- `readdir()`
- `closedir()`
- `uname()`

---

# 🚀 Compilation

Compile individual utilities:

```bash
gcc pwdx.c -o pwdx
gcc lsx.c -o lsx
gcc lsxi.c -o lsxi
gcc touchx.c -o touchx
gcc catx.c -o catx
gcc cpx.c -o cpx
gcc mvx.c -o mvx
gcc rmx.c -o rmx
gcc statx.c -o statx
gcc statxi.c -o statxi
gcc unamex.c -o unamex
gcc psx.c -o psx
```

Run any utility:

```bash
./utility_name [arguments]
```

